======================================================================

FUNCTION: vec_max_absvalue

DESCRIPTION: Find maximum absolute value of a vector

REQUIRES: ---

BUGS: ---

FUTURE IMPROVEMENTS: ---

----------------------------------------------------------------------

PROCESS DESCRIPTION:

  vec_max_absvalue(addr_srcVec:ESI,
                   vec_jumpSize:EBX,
                   numOfElements:ECX) maxAbsValue:XMM0 (single-preci.)

  Input parameters
      1) addr_srcVec   = Address to source vector
      2) vec_jumpSize  = ROWSIZE if column vector, otherwise COLUMNSIZE
      3) numOfElements = Number of elements to find

  Output parameters
      ---

  Returns
      maxAbsValue:XMM0 (single-precision)

  +-------------------------------------------------------------+
  |                   STACK MEMORY INFORMATION                  |
  +--------+----------------------------------------------------+
  | Offset |      Data       |           Description            |
  +--------+-----------------+----------------------------------+
  | +    0 | ---             | ---                              |
  |        |                 |                                  |
  +--------+-----------------+----------------------------------+
  | Total stack used for local variables =  0 bytes             |
  +-------------------------------------------------------------+

  Algorithm/Pseudocode is in "scilab/vec_max_absvalue.sce"

